8. Interpretation of results: Analyze the feature importance scores and use techniques such as Recursive Feature Elimination (RFE) if necessary for improving performance or reducing overfitting by eliminating less important features to create a more parsimonious, yet effective model.

10. Use the most successful model to predict target_material thickness on an unseen set of synthetic data, reporting accuracy metrics like RMSE and R^2 scores.

12. Validate the model with an independent test set of synthetic data points, ensuring that it can generalize well and doesn't overfit to the training data.
